data.sampled:
A. Using pascal's triangle to find the sum of all naturally numbered coefficients times each power of x, i.e., C(n, x) = n! / ( x!(n-x)! ), then we get ( n choose 0 ) * x^n + ( n choose 1 ) * x^( n - 1 ) + ... + ( n choose n-1 ) * x^1 + ( n choose n ) * x^0. In this sequence, we can find pairs with constant difference, e.g., (n choose 0 ) and ( n choose n ) always differ by exactly 6, so each pair difference is 2*6 = 12, thus n^2 - 12 = 6*x^n. n=6, we get x=6.
Ref:
https://artofproblemsolving.com/wiki/index.php?title=Taxicab_number.
Illustrative Example:
n=6, ( n choose 0 ) = 6! / ( 0!(6-0)! ) = 6 / 1 = 6, ( n choose n ) = 6! / ( 6!(6-6)! ) = 1 / 1 = 1, total = 20, the answer is right. n=7, ( n choose 0 ) = 7 ! / ( 0!(7-0)! ) = 5040, ( n choose 7 ) = 7! / ( 7!(7-7)! ) = 1 / 1 = 1, total = 5041, the answer is 6*7=42, almost near. So we think A is more reasonable.
